Exemplo de Regresso Simples Recursiva

par(ask=FALSE)
n<-1
X<- matrix(Boston$lstat)
N<-length(X)
y<-matrix(Boston$medv)
t<-numeric(2)
P<-500*diag(n+1)
mu<-1
for (i in 1:N){
  rls.step<-rls(c(1, X[i]),y[i],t,P,mu)
  t<-rls.step[[1]]
  P<-rls.step[[2]]
  if(i == N){
  plot(X[1:i],y[1:i],
       xlim=c(0,40),
       ylim=c(5,50),
       main=paste("Forgetting factor mu<-",mu))
  lines(X[1:i],cbind(array(1,c(i,1)), X[1:i])%*%t,
        col="red",
  )
  }
}

t
##            [,1]
## [1,] 34.5532737
## [2,] -0.9500153

source("recursiveRegression.R")
par(ask=FALSE)
n<-1
X<- cbind(Boston$lstat,Boston$rm)
N<-dim(X)[1]
y<-matrix(Boston$medv)
t<-numeric(3)
P<-500*diag(n+2)
mu<-1
for (i in 1:N){
  rls.step<-rls(c(1, X[i,]),y[i],t,P,mu)
  t<-rls.step[[1]]
  P<-rls.step[[2]]
}
t
